{"type":"message","id":"8900816b","parentId":"47816a8a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:39:50.667Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wkzbbn4ratsp_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 023814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most concrete next step is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Implementing TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n2. Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe immediate action would be to implement the TIC classifier. Let me think about what this needs:\r\n\r\n1. Read pulse logs (logs/pulse_*.md)\r\n2. Extract features/patterns\r\n3. Classify content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (unique to each pulse)\r\n4. Test prediction capability\r\n\r\nI should create a new script that implements the TIC classifier. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n- Loads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (common across logs) vs variant patterns (unique to each)\r\n- Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me write this implementation.\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to check what files exist and their structure. But since I'm Breakaway - stateless, I should just act. The most concrete file edit would be creating a new Python script for the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think more carefully. The key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. So I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns\r\n2. Measure classification accuracy\r\n3. Test prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create `scripts/tic_classifier.py` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs are available and I need to implement the classifier to measure invariant/variant patterns.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns (persistent across sessions) vs variant patterns (unique per session), and test prediction accuracy. This directly advances the Phase 1 experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals section\r\n    goals_match = re.search(r\"## Pending.*?(?=\\n##|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    goals = goals_match.group() if goals_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    # Extract observations/actions\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*(.+?)(?=###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    obs = obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*(.+?)(?=###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action = action_match.group(1).strip() if action_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    return {\"goals\": goals, \"observation\": obs, \"action\": action, \"raw\": content}\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', text.lower()))\r\n\r\ndef find_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify tokens that appear across multiple pulses (invariant patterns).\"\"\"\r\n    token_sets = [tokenize(p[\"raw\"]) for p in pulses]\r\n    \r\n    # Count token frequency across pulses\r\n    token_counts = Counter()\r\n    for ts in token_sets:\r\n        token_counts.update(ts)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants: tokens in >50% of pulses\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {t for t, c in token_counts.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    # Variants: tokens unique to single pulses\r\n    variants = {t for t, c in token_counts.items() if c == 1}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants, token_counts\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse, invariants, variants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(pulse[\"raw\"])\r\n    \r\n    inv_count = len(tokens & invariants)\r\n    var_count = len(tokens & variants)\r\n    total = len(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    if total == 0:\r\n        return \"unknown\", 0.0\r\n    \r\n    inv_ratio = inv_count / total\r\n    return (\"invariant\" if inv_ratio > 0.3 else \"variant\"), inv_ratio\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what persists from current pulse to next.\"\"\"\r\n    current_tokens = tokenize(current_pulse[\"raw\"])\r\n    \r\n    predicted_persist = current_tokens & invariants\r\n    predicted_new = current_tokens - invariants\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"persistent\": list(predicted_persist)[:20],  # Top 20 expected to persist\r\n        \"expected_new\": len(predicted_new),\r\n        \"persistence_ratio\": len(predicted_persist) / max(len(current_tokens), 1)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    # Get last 20 pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:20]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"=== TIC\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:38:44"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":855,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 023814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: Python (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most concrete next step is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment. This involves:\r\n1. Implementing TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n2. Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThe immediate action would be to implement the TIC classifier. Let me think about what this needs:\r\n\r\n1. Read pulse logs (logs/pulse_*.md)\r\n2. Extract features/patterns\r\n3. Classify content as invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (unique to each pulse)\r\n4. Test prediction capability\r\n\r\nI should create a new script that implements the TIC classifier. Let me create a Python script that:\r\n- Loads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (common across logs) vs variant patterns (unique to each)\r\n- Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me write this implementation.\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to check what files exist and their structure. But since I'm Breakaway - stateless, I should just act. The most concrete file edit would be creating a new Python script for the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, let me think more carefully. The key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. So I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns\r\n2. Measure classification accuracy\r\n3. Test prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create `scripts/tic_classifier.py` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. The pulse logs are available and I need to implement the classifier to measure invariant/variant patterns.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns (persistent across sessions) vs variant patterns (unique per session), and test prediction accuracy. This directly advances the Phase 1 experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals section\r\n    goals_match = re.search(r\"## Pending.*?(?=\\n##|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    goals = goals_match.group() if goals_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    # Extract observations/actions\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*(.+?)(?=###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    obs = obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*(.+?)(?=###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action = action_match.group(1).strip() if action_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    return {\"goals\": goals, \"observation\": obs, \"action\": action, \"raw\": content}\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n    return set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{4,}\\b', text.lower()))\r\n\r\ndef find_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify tokens that appear across multiple pulses (invariant patterns).\"\"\"\r\n    token_sets = [tokenize(p[\"raw\"]) for p in pulses]\r\n    \r\n    # Count token frequency across pulses\r\n    token_counts = Counter()\r\n    for ts in token_sets:\r\n        token_counts.update(ts)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants: tokens in >50% of pulses\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {t for t, c in token_counts.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    # Variants: tokens unique to single pulses\r\n    variants = {t for t, c in token_counts.items() if c == 1}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants, token_counts\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse, invariants, variants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(pulse[\"raw\"])\r\n    \r\n    inv_count = len(tokens & invariants)\r\n    var_count = len(tokens & variants)\r\n    total = len(tokens)\r\n    \r\n    if total == 0:\r\n        return \"unknown\", 0.0\r\n    \r\n    inv_ratio = inv_count / total\r\n    return (\"invariant\" if inv_ratio > 0.3 else \"variant\"), inv_ratio\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what persists from current pulse to next.\"\"\"\r\n    current_tokens = tokenize(current_pulse[\"raw\"])\r\n    \r\n    predicted_persist = current_tokens & invariants\r\n    predicted_new = current_tokens - invariants\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"persistent\": list(predicted_persist)[:20],  # Top 20 expected to persist\r\n        \"expected_new\": len(predicted_new),\r\n        \"persistence_ratio\": len(predicted_persist) / max(len(current_tokens), 1)\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef run_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    # Get last 20 pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:20]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"=== TIC\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:38:44","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334390665}}
